claim.claim-text:
13. A method of operating a mobile wireless network comprising:
receiving, by a provisioning server, a signal from a mobile wireless network specifying a transition condition has been met corresponding to a first mobile device having a first International Mobile Subscriber Identity (IMSI) and operating in the mobile wireless network under a first condition, the mobile wireless network including a plurality of mobile switching centers (MSCs) and a plurality of mobile devices operating in the mobile wireless network;
provisioning the first IMSI in the first HLR based on a state transition rule from a first provisioning state to a second provisioning state;
provisioning a second IMSI in the first HLR based on the state transition rule from a third provisioning state to the first provisioning state; and
transmitting a provisioning instruction to at least one of an Authentication Center (AuC), a Gateway GPRS Support Node (GGSN), a Billing system, or an Authentication Authorization Accounting (AAA) system according to the state transition rule.
